Description: Fragment of neck and rising oval handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine buff-brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '402'. Name Aristratos. An example from Isthmia is from the same die.
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (85)
